('Go Local at M Bloc Market',
'M Bloc Space, occupying over 2,000 square meters of a former Perum Peruri warehouse, offers a unique shopping experience with a focus on wellness, traceability, and locality. This modern toko kelontong, designed by M Bloc''s Building and Tenant Director Jacob Gatot Sura of Arcadia Architect, is dedicated to supporting independent, homegrown brands throughout the archipelago. The marketplace prioritizes well-being through its curated product selections, ensuring each item contributes to a healthier lifestyle. Traceability is emphasized, allowing consumers to understand the journey of products from production to their shopping bags. By supporting local production, the marketplace showcases the rich variety of products available within the archipelago, fostering community and sustainability. The founders of M Bloc Space delve into the concept of conscious shopping in urban settings. While conscious shopping often centers around ethical and eco-friendly practices, M Bloc Space broadens this idea to include product traceability. Under the leadership of co-founder Handoko Hendroyono, the marketplace team ensures the quality and authenticity of locally-made products. In collaboration with Peruri, they have developed a mobile app that allows shoppers to access detailed product descriptions and trace the origins of the brands. This initiative not only enhances consumer confidence but also promotes transparency in the shopping experience.',
'https://res.cloudinary.com/dxjm1mdjc/image/upload/v1746947031/6e06cc3c-b293-4b28-9706-ceb1cea00df6.png',
NULL,
'af22c765-095d-454d-a904-8ad9bf8cb249'),

('Aksara Bookstore: Epilogue for an era',
'Aksara is on a mission to highlight literary gems from smaller publishing companies, recognizing that these works are just as impressive and deserving of attention as those from larger publishers. To achieve this goal, Aksara has teamed up with POST, a local independent bookstore established in 2014 at Pasar Santa. Together, they aim to elevate indie and alternative literatures, focusing on bringing these lesser-known works into the spotlight.This collaboration curates a diverse collection of books from small and local publishers like Mojok, Lontar, and Post Santa. While the primary focus is on indie literature, the selection also includes national and international best-sellers, ensuring a wide range of choices. Whether you''re exploring a book from KPG''s The Comma Books or a renowned title from global giants like Penguin Books, the variety promises that every bookworm will find something captivating. Despite the store''s compact nature, the browsing experience at Aksara and POST is designed to be engaging, allowing visitors to discover new authors and titles that might otherwise remain obscured.',
